article.headline: UCF downs Tulane 73-65

images.name: M. Morgan made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by C. Reynolds.
images.caption: 1H (12:03) TULN Malik Morgan made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Cameron Reynolds.

article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- Daiquan Walker scored 20 points as UCF downed Tulane 73-65 on Wednesday night. Walker was 5 of 13 from the field and sank all eight of his free throws for the Knights (12-16, 6-11 American Conference). Freshman Tacko Fall added 17 points and 13 rebounds for his fourth double-double of the season. Adonys Henriquez had 16 points. Tulane jumped to a 21-9 lead midway through the first half but Fall brought UCF back with a pair of dunks and two layups in the final 4:11 to take a 33-32 lead at the break. The Knights extended their advantage to 52-41 on a Walker 3-pointer with 11:43 to play and led the rest of the way. Tulane cut it to 64-60 on a Cameron Reynolds dunk with 2:36 remaining but could not get closer. Malik Morgan scored 17 points with five rebounds, three assists and three steals for the Green Wave (10-20, 3-14).
